urls.title: Chapter 9 Public Bill Procedures
urls.description: The Standing Orders are the rules of procedure for the Parliament. 1. A “Public Bill” is any Bill introduced in the Parliament other than a Private Bill (as defined in Rule 9A.1). 2. The General Rules set out in Rules 9.2 to 9.13A apply in relation to every Public Bill other than a Hybrid Bill (as defined in Rule 9C.1), but where any of the Special Rules set out in Rules 9.14 to 9.21 apply in relation to the Bill, the Special Rule supersedes the General Rules to the extent that they are inconsistent. 1.
